tiers.ability_description: Whenever Dark Side allies grant a buff to another ally, that other ally recovers 3% Health and Protection.

The first time each Hutt Cartel ally falls below 50% Health, they gain Damage Immunity for 1 turn, which can't be copied, dispelled, or prevented.\n\nWhenever an enemy takes damage from a Thermal Detonator expiring, Hutt Cartel allies recover 5% Health and Protection, gain 5% Turn Meter, and there is a 50% chance that enemy is inflicted with a Thermal Detonator for 2 turns, which can't be dispelled, prevented, or resisted.

The max cooldown of Inventive is reduced by 1. Whenever Boushh inflicts Thermal Detonators on an enemy, inflict an additional Thermal Detonator for 2 turns and Hutt Cartel allies gain 10% Armor Penetration (max 70%) and 10% Turn Meter (once per turn).
Light Side allies recover 2% Health whenever they critically hit an enemy.
Whenever a Scoundrel ally deals damage to an enemy and no other enemy is Blinded, inflict Blind for 2 turns on the enemy, which can't be resisted.
Whenever IG-11 uses an ability, they deal more damage (max 100%) equal to half their Potency percentage. This effect will only trigger if IG-11 has more than 0% Potency.
Whenever Light Side allies start their turn, for each enemy with fewer than 4 debuffs, that ally gains 30% Potency until the end of the turn.
Whenever an enemy is defeated by a Scoundrel ally, that enemy can't be revived.
Whenever Cara Dune removes Turn Meter from an enemy, she deals damage to them equal to 25% of their Max Health.
Whenever Light Side allies start their turn, for each enemy with fewer than 4 debuffs, that ally gains 30% Potency until the end of the turn.
The first time each Scoundrel ally uses a Basic ability on their turn, reset their cooldowns and gain 100% Turn Meter. Limit once per character per battle.
Whenever Dark Side allies grant a buff to another ally, that other ally recovers 3% Health and Protection.
The first time each Hutt Cartel ally falls below 50% Health, all Hutt Cartel allies reduce their cooldowns by 1 and gain 10% Turn Meter.
Cad Bane deals 5% more damage per Relic Amplifier level on all allies present at the start of battle.
Dark Side allies recover 2% Health whenever they critically hit an enemy.
The first time each Tusken ally falls below 50% Health they gain Damage Immunity for 1 turn and gain Health Steal Up for 2 turns.

Tusken Warrior starts the encounter with 10 stacks of Momentum for 3 turns. Whenever Tusken Warrior gains Momentum, she also gains 2% Critical Damage and Defense Penetration per stack for the rest of the encounter. Whenever Finishing Strikes defeats an enemy, they can't be revived and then revive all Tusken allies at the end of the turn if there is at least one Tusken ally active.
Whenever Light Side allies grant a buff to another ally, that other ally recovers 3% Health and Protection.
Whenever an enemy is defeated by a Scoundrel ally, that enemy can't be revived.
Whenever L3-37 deals damage, she deals additional Physical damage equal to 25% of her Max Health. Whenever L3-37 gains Prepared, she gains 15% Turn Meter.
Whenever Light Side allies inflict a debuff, they gain 2% Critical Chance (stacking) for 3 turns.
Whenever Rebel Fighter allies lose a stack of Heal Over Time, they gain a stack of Heal Over Time (10%) for 2 turns.

If the allied leader is a Rebel Fighter: Whenever an ally gains a stack of Heal Over Time, Chirrut Îmwe and Baze Malbus gain 10% Offense (stacking) until the end of battle. Chirrut also gains 5% Turn Meter (limit once per turn). Whenever he uses a Basic ability, Baze Malbus is called to assist.
Whenever Light Side allies inflict a debuff, they gain 2% Critical Chance (stacking) for 3 turns.
Whenever Mandalorian allies grant a buff to another ally, that ally gains 10% Turn Meter (limit once per turn per ally).
The Mandalorian gains 15% Turn Meter when other allies use a Special ability on their turn.
Whenever Light Side allies inflict a debuff, they gain 2% Critical Chance (stacking) for 3 turns.
The first time each Rebel Fighter ally falls below 50% Health, all Rebel Fighter allies reduce their cooldowns by 1 and gain 10% Turn Meter.
Whenever another ally attacks during Biggs Darklighter's turn, Biggs Darklighter and that ally gain 25% Turn Meter.
The first time each Dark Side ally reaches 90%, 70%, and 50% Health inflict Doubt on a random enemy that doesn't have it for 2 turns, which can't be dispelled or prevented.
Whenever Empire allies critically hit an enemy during their turn, that ally gains 10% Offense (stacking) for 2 turns.
The first time Death Trooper is defeated, they are revived with 100% Health, gain Protection Over Time (75%) for 2 turns, and take a bonus turn.
The first time each Dark Side ally reaches 90%, 70%, and 50% Health inflict Doubt on a random enemy that doesn't have it for 2 turns, which can't be dispelled or prevented.
Whenever an enemy loses Turn Meter, Empire allies gain Protection Up (stacking, 10%) for 2 turns.  Whenever an ally loses Protection Up they gain 10% Turn Meter.

At the start of battle, Imperial Probe Droid loses all Protection and gains that much Max Health. Imperial Probe Droid can be revived after using Self-Destruct and ignores Taunt.  Whenever Imperial Probe Droid uses Self-Destruct, the target enemy takes additional True damage equal to 50% of Imperial Probe Droid's Max Health, which can't be evaded.
Whenever Light Side allies inflict a debuff, they gain 2% Critical Chance (stacking) for 3 turns.
Whenever an enemy is defeated by a Mandalorian ally, that enemy can't be revived.

After using Disciplined Set Up, until he uses Swift Takedown, The Mandalorian (Beskar Armor) can't be defeated and is immune to Fear, Stun, and Turn Meter reduction. Swift Takedown deals 20% more damage for each stack of Whistling Birds The Mandalorian (Beskar Armor) had at the start of the turn.
Whenever Dark Side allies inflict a debuff on an enemy, they deal damage to that enemy equal to 2% of that enemy's Max Health.
At the start of their first turn, Empire allies gain Offense equal to 400% of their current Defense. Then they lose 50% Defense.

At the start of battle and whenever Dark Trooper Moff Gideon uses a Special ability, if the allied slot is available and there is no ally Dark Trooper, summon a Dark Trooper. Otherwise, a summoned ally Dark Trooper gains a stack of Dark Trooper Squad.\n\nWhenever an ally uses a Special ability, all Moff Gideons gain a stack of Insight. Imperial Remnant allies have +15% Defense and Offense for each stack of Insight on Moff Gideons.
